Police arrested more than 600 suspects on various charges, including possession of counterfeit goods and undocumented persons. 

Those arrested were kept at Johannesburg Central police station for verification. 

Police Minister, Bheki Cele, and his Department of International Relations and Co-Operations counterpart, Minister Naledi Pandor, have since urged people living in South Africa to stop confusing crime and illegal activities with xenophobia. 

